         <abstract>
            <p>A Church service made up of psalms, biblical readings and hymns. This record is the general one to be used when the recension of the
               work cannot be identified.
               Four types of <foreign xml:lang="gez">Saʿātāt</foreign> have been identified by <bibl>
                  <ptr target="bm:Taft1986Liturgy"/>
                  <citedRange unit="page">266</citedRange>
               </bibl>:</p>
            <p> 
               <ref type="work" corresp="LIT2230Saatat"/>: the Coptic <foreign xml:lang="gez">Saʿātāt</foreign>;</p>
            <p> 
               <ref type="work" corresp="LIT3575Mashaf"/>: the <foreign xml:lang="gez">Saʿātāt</foreign> of <persName ref="PRS4709Giyorgis">Giyorgis of Saglā</persName>, 
               which replaced the <ref type="work" corresp="LIT2230Saatat"/>:  and is presently in use in Ethiopia and Eritrea;</p>
            <p>
               <ref type="work" corresp="LIT3576Saatat"/>:  a <foreign xml:lang="gez">Saʿātāt</foreign> that includes the entire Psalter in the daily pensum;</p>
            <p>
               <ref type="work" corresp="LIT3577GizeS"/>: a cursus of prayers which is not really a <foreign xml:lang="gez">Saʿātāt</foreign>, but a <foreign xml:lang="gez">Gize ṣalot</foreign> for hermits and recluses.</p>
         </abstract>
